Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A. is a vocabulary and set of grammatical rules for instructing a computer or computing device to perform specific tasks




What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. JDK stands for Java Runtime Environment which includes Java Virtual Machine. It has different components and some of them are:

   Java Compiler - converts source code into java bytecode
   Java Interpreter - interprets class file generated by compiler
   Java Disassembler - disassembles class file
   Java Documentation - creates documentation from source code comment
   Java Debugger - tests and debug java program
   Java Applet Viewer - can be used to run and debug Java applet





What is IDE?
A.Integrated Development Environment




What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A.Eclipse, IntelliJ, NetBeans, BlueJ



Explain the entire java life cycle.
- In the first step, source code is written using a text editor and saved as a .java file. It is then passed to Java compiler which transformed the source code to byte code and creates a .class file. The .class file is loaded to JVM which converts the code to machine understandable language and pass to operating system which present the output of the code.


what is class?
- Where you define your objects

What is object?
- Is a combination of data and procedures working on the available data, The state of an object is stored in fields (variables), while methods (functions) display the object's behavior.

What is the entry point of an application?
- The "main" method is the entry point of an application in java

Why main is static?
- The main method is static because it can be initiated without creating an instance of it

Which class is the superclass of all classes?
- The “Object”(java.lang.object) class is at the root/base level of the Class hierarchy in Java.

What is difference between path and classpath variables?
- PATH is an environment variable. It is used by operating system to find the executable files (.exe) or in other words java binaries (java or javac).
    CLASSPATH is also an environment variable used by Application ClassLoader to locate and load the .class files(compiled java bytecodes)

What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
- In interface class, you can't implement any method but in abstract class you are allowed to implement non-abstract method.

Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
- No. You use "new" to create an object from an interface and abstract class

what is Access Specifier?
- Access specifier are keywords to set accessibility of classes, methods and variable. Public, Private, Protected.

What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
- -Object Oriented Programming
  Abstraction - a way to hide implementation from interface
  Encapsulation - is a form of data hiding
  Inheritance - is a process by which one object acquires all the properties of parent object
  Polymorphism - is the ability of an object to take on many forms

What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
- A Java package organizes Java classes into namespaces, providing a unique namespace for each type it contains, is more likely a folder in which you have documents. 

What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
- Application Programming Interface. File Reader and Buffer Reader

