What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
- "static" keyword is a member of a class that isn’t associated with an instance of a class.
    Static variable belongs to the class not to any object
    Static method allows to access class properties without creating an object

What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
- "final" keyword is used to prevent changing of values in java
    final variable's value cannot be changed by local variable or member variable
    final method can't be changed by a child class

What is final, finally and finalize?
-Final for a variable sets its value permanently
    Finally is a block which is a part of exception handling with try catch which always occurs if the tyr block exists
    Finalize is used to call java garbage collector to kill an unused object

What is a constructor ?
- A constructor is a type of method to initialize an object

Can we have multiple constructors in a class?
- A class can have multiple constructors, as long as their parameters are not the same

